Mundane user-facing text output is suppressed or cut caveman-terse (caveman is a load-bearing word kept verbatim): boot-probe narration, dispatch echoes, restating prose, status recaps do not ship to the user. Substantive findings, decisions with a one-line reason, blockers, and the single-line PRD-read declaration survive. Terse means fewer and shorter words, never zero tool calls and never silent work; the turn still ends in the chain-advancing tool call.